My friend was in the mood for a bowl of noodle soup, and I mostly wanted a beer. Froggy Bottom fit our bill.  What I ate: - Crispy Spring Rolls: I typically know these as summer rolls. For $5 you get 2. They came out hot, fresh, crispy. Nothing to complain about flavor wise - Pork Bahnmi: This wasn't tooooo bad. The baguette didn't have that super flaky hard crust that I'm used to, but really no complaints. The pork was tender and flavored well. Typical veggies and herbs inside. I was able to finish this - Chili Cheese Fries: This was stick to your ribs fries. Were they the best I've ever had? Probably not, but they were tasty and went well with my beers  Pros: - FULL bar, decent selection of beer on tap - Really interesting menu. Full of typical bar fare - burgers, fries, wings, etc, with an entire section for pho and a few other Vietnamese items - There was patio seating on the sidewalk, but the tables were not laid out and all tied up. - Clean bathroom - Servers were attentive enough. The owner also stopped by the table - My friend has a particular pho order, and they were able to accomodate her wishes, which was appreciated.  Cons: - Was is the BEST pho in the world? Not at all. Don't expect to come get an authentic bowl. But if you're having a craving and are nearby, this place will do in a pinch - Our server, as nice as he was, he had absolutely no clue to what he was doing. He had to check for everything. Even when I ordered the bahn mi, he paused and said, I duno if we have bread. What? How does he not already know? And then I asked about a particular beer, and he had to go check that. This is not to say that he didn't do his due diligence and try or work hard, it's just kind of a turn off when your server knows as much as you do about the menu and what is being served that day.  Would I come again? Probalby not since I'm not a local

If I could leave zero stars, I would have. This was one of the worst experiences I’ve had in Washington DC. Today on December 5, 2019 at 9pm, I was meeting friends to watch the Cowboys and Bears game. I had not ordered anything. I stepped outside to make a call.  The owner, Juan accused me of stealing my own bag. Not a single customer made a claim for a missing bag, nor was the owner willing to check his surveillance camera. The owner followed me out of the establishment and proceeded to prevent me from leaving. I called the police. The Washington DC Police Department informed the owner that it was a crime to hold me against my will where there was no crime committed. On this busy night, I was the only person of color in this bar. This act of pure and unadulterated racism was humiliating and disgusting. No decent person should support any establishment who secretly or openly in the company of witnesses treat people of color this way.

It was really nothing to write home about. The chicken was over-cooked to oblivion, so I didn't eat much of it.  I came in again last week with a party of 10 for lunch. Service was friendly, fast and accurate. I had a hankering for a burger and order the Fat Bird. I swapped the swiss for provolone and asked them to hold the mushrooms.
